HEADWORD: Priapism
<hw>Pri"a*pism</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>priapismus</ets>, Gr.
<?/, from <ets>Priapus</ets> the god of procreation, the penis, Gr. <?/:
cf. F. <ets>priapisme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>More or less
permanent erection and rigidity of the penis, with or without sexual
desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Priapulacea</ent>⟦br⟧
